entry.title: tflite/mediapipe/eigen: avoid exposing flags to disable warnings
entry.content:
eigen's config contains a handful of flags that disable warnings.

tflite was depending on this config via a public_config, which

means any code using tflite was inheriting a bunch of flags that

disable warnings. This is risky, and not something we should do.



This patch splits eigen's config into two. The one that tflite

depends upon via public_config does not disable any warnings. This

means code using tflite no longer disables a bunch of compiler

warnings. As a result of this I needed to add some flags to disable

warnings in other code that was picking up the flags from eigen.

That this code needs to disable warnings is not new, it was masked

by eigen's config.



This also adds -Wno-unused-function to tflite as this was masked

by flags from eigen. Without it the following error is generated:



../../third_party/tflite/src/tensorflow/lite/kernels/internal/optimized/neon_tensor_utils.cc:587:13: error: unused function 'DotprodMatrixBatchFourVectorMultiplyAccumulate' [-Werror,-Wunused-function]

587 | static void DotprodMatrixBatchFourVectorMultiplyAccumulate(

| ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

1 error generated.

entry.title: [web-tests] Deflake two harness exception handling tests
entry.content:
Two recently reenabled `run_web_tests.py` integration tests [0] that use

real subprocesses cause the harness to hang flakily [1, 2].

`test_keyboard_interrupt` and `test_exception_raised` raise exceptions

in the worker process that are relayed to the manager process.



For reliability reasons [4], the worker will not exit until all of its

buffered messages to the manager have been transferred to the queue's

underlying OS pipe. However, there can be a deadlock if the pipe is

full: the worker waiting for space in the queue, and the manager waiting

for the worker to join.



When cleaning up, the manager should first flush the queue so that

workers have space to enqueue messages. Also, don't install real signal

handlers in the test.



[3] encountered a very similar issue.



[0]: https://crrev.com/c/4707085

[1]: https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/Linux%20Tests/136179/overview

[2]: https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/Linux%20Tests/136167/overview

[3]: https://github.com/web-platform-tests/wpt/pull/41504

entry.title: Reland "Add SurfaceFrameType::OVERLAP"
entry.content:
This is a reland of commit f98b46d820185457aa44cef8a06e4f8388fb86a3.

The revert of the aforementioned commit was an attempt to fix

browser_tests failures, but after the revert the tests are still

failing. Therefore, the commit should not be the culprit change.



Different from the original change, the reland commit improved the way

of communicating the position of the client window.



Original change's description:

> Add SurfaceFrameType::OVERLAP

>

> As part of the shelf/caption insets separation project, we need to

> place caption(header) in front of(z-axis) the window area instead of

> putting it above(y-axis) the area.

>

> This commit utilizes the existing wayland protocol `setFrame` and adds

> a new enum SurfaceFrameType::OVERLAP to implement this feature. To

> support SurfaceFrameType::OVERLAP, the change adjusts the way to

> calculate window/client bounds, and to perform nonClientHitTest.

>

> We also considered creating a new protocol for ARC to communicate the

> position of caption. However, reusing the `setFrame()` function seems to

> be a better solution.

> For more details see go/arc-t-caption-migration-wayland.

>

entry.title: [Viewport Segments API] Fix fullscreen video playback when the device is folded
entry.content:
When the device is folded (and for PCs the keyboard is detached), the

fullscreen video is laid across the fold which is not a great user

experience. This patch fixes the issue by putting the video in one

segment only.



fullscreen.css is a user agent style sheet and do not support CSS environment

variables and media queries. CSS environment variables are correctly

parsed but not resolved. In order to make the patch simple only the

Viewport Segments variables will be resolved. In regards to MQs we now

enable parsing them and resolving them the first time. However in this

patch the MQs will only be re-evaluated when the Viewport Segments changes.



This patch will only impact non-foldable devices when parsing the fullscreen.css

as we now parse MQs which we didn't before, but said MQs will be evaluated

once (to none) and never re-evaluated.

entry.title: [Sync] Notify observers when data types stopped due to preconditions
entry.content:
Prior to this CL, OnSingleDataTypeWillStop() ignored any failures which

are already in DataTypeStatusTable, which was supposed to detect new

failures only. But DataTypePreconditionChanged() updates the table first

and only then stops the data type (which will eventually call

OnSingleDataTypeWillStop), so in practice it's a new failure which is

ignored, hence no reconfiguration is happening and observers are not

notified about the changes.



This CL also fixes data type precondition update code path because it

could start DataTypeManager configuration before the sync engine is

initialized (and hence violate some DCHECKs). Now any precondition

changes are ignored if data type manager is stopped.



Clearing metadata for stopped types is also moved to ModelLoadManager

similar to disabled types.

entry.title: Cellular: Start using the last seen network instead of ICCID for sms.
entry.content:
In tests by eng prod it was discovered that on certain devices

the text messages were not being blocked. Upon investigation,

we found out that this happens because sometimes the ICCID

device property is set after the sms device handler has been

initialized which causes the GUID to always be empty.

In this CL we add a code path that starts using the last

connected network instead of ICCID to prevent this issue.
